        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 4:47PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Redbone, or near
Barnesville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Barnesville, Forsyth, Redbone, Goggins, Collier, Johnstonville, and
Brent.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
